### Annual Assessment Activities

**Control Effectiveness Full Review**

Annually, the ISSO conducts a structured review of the full SSP — not a re-assessment in the formal NIST SP 800-53A sense, but a thorough self-evaluation of whether each control family is functioning as documented.

This review is less rigorous than the formal external assessment (which happens at re-authorization) but more rigorous than the ongoing weekly and monthly checks. It produces the annual continuous monitoring summary that the AO receives per Condition 4 of the authorization.

**Annual continuous monitoring summary for AO:**
- Summary of security events and incidents during the year (count, severity, disposition)
- POA&M item completion status: items closed, items revised, items added
- Vulnerability management trend: vulnerability scan finding severity trend over 12 months
- Control effectiveness self-assessment: any controls where the ISSO has identified degradation concerns
- Changes to threat environment relevant to the system
- ISSO recommendation: continue current authorization, begin early re-authorization planning, or flag material risk change requiring AO decision

